# Jetpack Compose Best Practices (Latest Standards)

* Use the latest stable versions of Jetpack Compose libraries as per the [official release notes](mdc:https:/developer.android.com/jetpack/androidx/releases/compose).
* Follow Material 3 guidelines for theming and UI components.
* Use `@Composable` functions for all UI, and prefer stateless composables unless state is required.
* Use `StateFlow` or `MutableStateFlow` for state management in ViewModels.
* Use `remember` and `rememberSaveable` for local state in composables.
* Use `Modifier` chaining for layout, styling, and interaction.
* Use `LaunchedEffect`, `SideEffect`, and `DisposableEffect` for side effects and lifecycle-aware code.
* Use `Navigation Compose` for in-app navigation.
* Use `LazyColumn`, `LazyRow`, and other lazy layouts for lists and grids.
* Use `Scaffold` and `Surface` for structure and theming.
* Use `@OptIn` annotation for experimental APIs, and prefer stable APIs when possible.
